<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-12-19T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-12-19T04:00:00-05:00" n="638" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d638">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3241: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-19T17:00:00+08:00">December 19, 1931—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 19—8:55 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Doctor Koo has just asked me to confirm to him a Reuter’s report dated
                            Washington, December 18, to the effect that the United States had
                            addressed a further note to Japan in regard to Manchuria expressing <pb facs="0806" n="696" xml:id="pg_696"/> solicitude that Japan’s
                            obligations under the Washington Nine-Power Treaty and the
                            Kellogg-Briand Pact should be respected. Can the Department give me
                            information for Koo?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>